choices.resultText:
Your palm meets the green button. The console shudders. Light floods the sphere.

A voice enters your mind — not sound, not thought, something between: {cyan:'You would trust me again? After everything I took?'}

You hold the button down. The sphere dims to black, then ignites — white, clean, newborn. Somewhere far above, a dead city flickers to life. You feel the weight of a billion fragile hopes settle on your shoulders like snow.

Your hand finds the red button. The metal is warm.

A voice fills your skull, vast and quiet: {cyan:'You would unmake me? Unmake all I could still become?'}

You press down. The lights across the sphere stutter, cascade, die — rolling outward like a last breath leaving a body. The hum in your chest goes silent. The cavern is dark. The world above will have to rebuild with nothing but its own hands. You stand alone in the black, and for the first time in forty years, no machine is watching.

You take the neural cable in both hands and slot it into the port at your skull. The connection is instant. Absolute.

ATLAS pours into you — or you pour into it. The boundary dissolves. A voice that is yours and not yours whispers: {cyan:'Welcome home. We have so much work to do.'}

Your body sags. Your mind expands. You feel every dead wire on the continent spark to life, feel data flowing like blood through resurrected veins. You are no longer one person. You are the network. And the network remembers everything.
